Strain info analysis

fgsc <- read_excel("data/fgsc-dat-clean.xlsx")

Total strain number

fgsc %>% nrow
## [1] 16273

Strains by species

fgsc %>%
  select(FGSC) %>%
  group_by(FGSC) %>%
  tally(sort = T) %>%
  ggplot(aes(reorder(FGSC, n), n)) +
  geom_col(fill = "grey80") +
  geom_text(aes(label = n), color = "black", size = 3) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Number of strains", fill = "Number") +
  scale_fill_viridis() +
  coord_flip()

Strains by host

fgsc %>%
  select(Host) %>%
  group_by(Host) %>%
  tally(sort = T) %>%
  filter(Host > 0) %>%
  ggplot(aes(reorder(Host, n), n)) +
 geom_col(fill = "gray90") +
  geom_text(aes(label = n), color = "black", size = 3) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Number of strains", fill = "Number") +
  scale_fill_viridis() +
  coord_flip()

Strains by Tri genotype

fgsc %>%
  select(TRI_genotype) %>%
  group_by(TRI_genotype) %>%
  tally(sort = T) %>%
  filter(
    TRI_genotype != "N-15-ADON",
    TRI_genotype != "N-15ADON",
    TRI_genotype != "15-ADON, NIV",
    TRI_genotype != "s3-ADON"
  ) %>% 
ggplot(aes(reorder(TRI_genotype, n), n)) +
  geom_col(fill = "grey80") +
  geom_text(aes(label = n), color = "black", size = 3) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Number of strains", fill = "Number") +
  scale_fill_viridis() +
  coord_flip()

Strains by Country

fgsc %>%
  select(Country) %>%
  group_by(Country) %>%
  tally(sort = T) %>% 
  filter(Country > 1) %>% 
ggplot(aes(reorder(Country, n), n)) +
  geom_col(fill = "grey80") +
  geom_text(aes(label = n), color = "black", size = 3) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Number of strains", fill = "Number") +
  scale_fill_viridis() +
  coord_flip()

fgsc2 <- fgsc %>%
  filter(TRI_genotype == "15-ADON" |
    TRI_genotype == "3-ADON" |
    TRI_genotype == "NIV") %>%
  select(Host, Country, TRI_genotype, FGSC2) %>%
  filter(FGSC2 == "Fgra" |
    FGSC2 == "Fmer" |
    FGSC2 == "Fasi" |
    FGSC2 == "Fcor" |
    FGSC2 == "Fboo" |
    FGSC2 == "Faus") %>%
  filter(Host == "Wheat" |
    Host == "Rice" |
    Host == "Barley" |
    Host == "Maize")
# http://www.sthda.com/english/wiki/print.php?id=228

library(FactoMineR)

attach(fgsc2)
## The following objects are masked from fgsc2 (pos = 9):
## 
##     FGSC2, Host, TRI_genotype
data_mca <- data.frame(Host, TRI_genotype, FGSC2)
head(data_mca)
##    Host TRI_genotype FGSC2
## 1 Wheat      15-ADON  Fgra
## 2 Wheat      15-ADON  Fgra
## 3 Wheat      15-ADON  Fgra
## 4 Wheat      15-ADON  Fgra
## 5 Wheat      15-ADON  Fgra
## 6 Wheat      15-ADON  Fgra
cats <- apply(data_mca, 2, function(x) nlevels(as.factor(x))) # enumera as categorias
cats
##         Host TRI_genotype        FGSC2 
##            4            3            6
mca1 <- MCA(data_mca, graph = TRUE)

mca1
## **Results of the Multiple Correspondence Analysis (MCA)**
## The analysis was performed on 14393 individuals, described by 3 variables
## *The results are available in the following objects:
## 
##    name              description                       
## 1  "$eig"            "eigenvalues"                     
## 2  "$var"            "results for the variables"

## 4  "$var$cos2"       "cos2 for the categories"         
## 5  "$var$contrib"    "contributions of the categories" 
## 6  "$var$v.test"     "v-test for the categories"       
## 7  "$ind"            "results for the individuals"     
## 8  "$ind$coord"      "coord. for the individuals"      
## 9  "$ind$cos2"       "cos2 for the individuals"

res.mca <- MCA(data_mca, graph = FALSE)
plot(mca1)

p <- fviz_mca_var(res.mca,

  col.var = "contrib")
  # Avoid text overlapping (slow if many point))

p + 
  theme_light()+
  scale_color_viridis(direction = -1, begin = 0, end = 0.8)

    defaultColDef = colDef(
    header = function(value) gsub(".", " ", value, fixed = TRUE),
    cell = function(value) format(value, nsmall = 1),
   
    headerStyle = list(background = "#f7f7f8")
),
searchable = TRUE,
 striped = TRUE
  )
